
@startuml

' Define classes and their attributes
class Bank {
    +String name
}

class Branch {
    +String address
}

class Customer {
    +String firstName
    +String lastName
}

class Account {
    +int accountNumber
    +double balance
}

class CurrentAccount {
    +double overdraftLimit
}

class SavingsAccount {}

' Relationships
Bank "1" *-- "many" Branch : has
Bank "1" *-- "many" Customer : manages
Customer "1..5" --> "1" Account : owns
Account <|-- CurrentAccount
Account <|-- SavingsAccount

@enduml

### Explanation of the Diagram:
- **Bank**: Has many `Branch` objects and manages many `Customer` objects.
- **Customer**: Each customer can own 1 to 5 accounts.
- **Account**: Abstract base class with common properties (`accountNumber`, `balance`). Inherited by `CurrentAccount` and `SavingsAccount`.
- **CurrentAccount**: Extends `Account` and adds an `overdraftLimit`.

